title: Convergence in law and weak convergence
type: text/vnd.tiddlywiki

Let $$X_n \sim \mu_n,\;X \sim \mu$$ be $$\R^d$$-valued random variables. Then $$X_n \xrightarrow{\mathscr{L}} X$$ if and only if $$\mu_n \rightharpoonup \mu$$ in $$\smoothcs(\R^d, \R)'$$ or $$\smoothbd(\R^d, \R)'$$.